
To build and use jaim, you will need the following:

 - macOS on arm64 (Apple Silicon)

 - A C++ compiler with C++23 support (Xcode 16+ / Apple clang 18+)

 - Autoconf, automake, and optionally pandoc (to format the man page)

To build from a git checkout, run:

    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure
    make

To build from a release tarball, run:

    ./configure
    make

To install:

    make install

To override the installation prefix:

    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local
    make
    make install

jaim uses macOS sandbox profiles (Seatbelt) to restrict sandboxed
processes.  Unlike the Linux version (jai), it does not require root
privileges or setuid installation.
